{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":498,"text":"Five years ago, I was a Ph.D. student"},{"time":3097,"text":"living two lives."},{"time":4741,"text":"In one, I used NASA supercomputers"},{"time":7057,"text":"to design next-generation spacecraft,"},{"time":9785,"text":"and in the other I was a data scientist"},{"time":12364,"text":"looking for potential smugglers"},{"time":14783,"text":"of sensitive nuclear technologies."},{"time":18022,"text":"As a data scientist, I did a lot of analyses,"},{"time":20881,"text":"mostly of facilities,"},{"time":22348,"text":"industrial facilities around the world."},{"time":24619,"text":"And I was always looking for a better canvas"},{"time":27307,"text":"to tie these all together."},{"time":29373,"text":"And one day, I was thinking about how"},{"time":31239,"text":"all data has a location,"},{"time":33363,"text":"and I realized that the answer"},{"time":35096,"text":"had been staring me in the face."},{"time":36984,"text":"Although I was a satellite engineer,"},{"time":39622,"text":"I hadn't thought about using satellite imagery"},{"time":42793,"text":"in my work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44359,"text":"Now, like most of us, I'd been online,"},{"time":46306,"text":"I'd see my house, so I thought,"},{"time":48088,"text":"I'll hop in there and I'll start looking up"},{"time":50386,"text":"some of these facilities."},{"time":51803,"text":"And what I found really surprised me."},{"time":53772,"text":"The pictures that I was finding"},{"time":55446,"text":"were years out of date,"},{"time":57347,"text":"and because of that,"},{"time":58415,"text":"it had relatively little relevance"},{"time":60086,"text":"to the work that I was doing today."},{"time":62546,"text":"But I was intrigued."},{"time":64007,"text":"I mean, satellite imagery is pretty amazing stuff."},{"time":67243,"text":"There are millions and millions of sensors"},{"time":69546,"text":"surrounding us today,"},{"time":70990,"text":"but there's still so much we\ndon't know on a daily basis."},{"time":73950,"text":"How much oil is stored in all of China?"},{"time":77703,"text":"How much corn is being produced?"},{"time":80636,"text":"How many ships are in all of our world's ports?"},{"time":84707,"text":"Now, in theory, all of these questions"},{"time":87266,"text":"could be answered by imagery,"},{"time":89510,"text":"but not if it's old."},{"time":91237,"text":"And if this data was so valuable,"},{"time":93695,"text":"then how come I couldn't get my hands"},{"time":95627,"text":"on more recent pictures?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":98177,"text":"So the story begins over 50 years ago"},{"time":101312,"text":"with the launch of the first generation"},{"time":103183,"text":"of U.S. government photo reconnaissance satellites."},{"time":106783,"text":"And today, there's a handful"},{"time":108479,"text":"of the great, great grandchildren"},{"time":110674,"text":"of these early Cold War machines"},{"time":112339,"text":"which are now operated by private companies"},{"time":114348,"text":"and from which the vast majority of satellite imagery"},{"time":117057,"text":"that you and I see on a daily basis comes."},{"time":119882,"text":"During this period, launching things into space,"},{"time":122796,"text":"just the rocket to get the satellite up there,"},{"time":125473,"text":"has cost hundreds of millions of dollars each,"},{"time":130074,"text":"and that's created tremendous pressure"},{"time":131826,"text":"to launch things infrequently"},{"time":134115,"text":"and to make sure that when you do,"},{"time":135459,"text":"you cram as much functionality in there as possible."},{"time":139098,"text":"All of this has only made satellites"},{"time":140709,"text":"bigger and bigger and bigger"},{"time":143126,"text":"and more expensive,"},{"time":144724,"text":"now nearly a billion, with a b, dollars per copy."},{"time":149761,"text":"Because they are so expensive,"},{"time":151460,"text":"there aren't very many of them."},{"time":152927,"text":"Because there aren't very many of them,"},{"time":154272,"text":"the pictures that we see on a daily basis"},{"time":156728,"text":"tend to be old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158232,"text":"I think a lot of people actually\nunderstand this anecdotally,"},{"time":161514,"text":"but in order to visualize just how sparsely"},{"time":164053,"text":"our planet is collected,"},{"time":165937,"text":"some friends and I put together a dataset"},{"time":168003,"text":"of the 30 million pictures that have been gathered"},{"time":170590,"text":"by these satellites between 2000 and 2010."},{"time":174074,"text":"As you can see in blue, huge areas of our world"},{"time":176829,"text":"are barely seen, less than once a year,"},{"time":179619,"text":"and even the areas that are seen most frequently,"},{"time":181891,"text":"those in red, are seen at best once a quarter."},{"time":185639,"text":"Now as aerospace engineering grad students,"},{"time":188555,"text":"this chart cried out to us as a challenge."},{"time":191983,"text":"Why do these things have to be so expensive?"},{"time":195438,"text":"Does a single satellite really have to cost"},{"time":198173,"text":"the equivalent of three 747 jumbo jets?"},{"time":202936,"text":"Wasn't there a way to build a smaller,"},{"time":205099,"text":"simpler, new satellite design that could enable"},{"time":208271,"text":"more timely imaging?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210289,"text":"I realize that it does sound a little bit crazy"},{"time":213740,"text":"that we were going to go out and just"},{"time":215251,"text":"begin designing satellites,"},{"time":217098,"text":"but fortunately we had help."},{"time":219061,"text":"In the late 1990s, a couple of professors"},{"time":221996,"text":"proposed a concept for radically reducing the price"},{"time":225477,"text":"of putting things in space."},{"time":227249,"text":"This was hitchhiking small satellites"},{"time":229360,"text":"alongside much larger satellites."},{"time":232376,"text":"This dropped the cost of putting objects up there"},{"time":235285,"text":"by over a factor of 100,"},{"time":237283,"text":"and suddenly we could afford to experiment,"},{"time":240369,"text":"to take a little bit of risk,"},{"time":241837,"text":"and to realize a lot of innovation."},{"time":244103,"text":"And a new generation of engineers and scientists,"},{"time":247192,"text":"mostly out of universities,"},{"time":248791,"text":"began launching these very small,"},{"time":251134,"text":"breadbox-sized satellites called CubeSats."},{"time":253725,"text":"And these were built with electronics obtained"},{"time":256128,"text":"from RadioShack instead of Lockheed Martin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260026,"text":"Now it was using the lessons\nlearned from these early missions"},{"time":262866,"text":"that my friends and I began a series of sketches"},{"time":265561,"text":"of our own satellite design."},{"time":267250,"text":"And I can't remember a specific day"},{"time":270034,"text":"where we made a conscious decision"},{"time":271894,"text":"that we were actually going to\ngo out and build these things,"},{"time":274529,"text":"but once we got that idea in our minds"},{"time":276959,"text":"of the world as a dataset,"},{"time":279120,"text":"of being able to capture millions of data points"},{"time":281610,"text":"on a daily basis describing the global economy,"},{"time":284663,"text":"of being able to unearth billions of connections"},{"time":287183,"text":"between them that had never before been found,"},{"time":290348,"text":"it just seemed boring"},{"time":291996,"text":"to go work on anything else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294903,"text":"And so we moved into a cramped,"},{"time":297876,"text":"windowless office in Palo Alto,"},{"time":300855,"text":"and began working to take our design"},{"time":302822,"text":"from the drawing board into the lab."},{"time":305760,"text":"The first major question we had to tackle"},{"time":308418,"text":"was just how big to build this thing."},{"time":310752,"text":"In space, size drives cost,"},{"time":313935,"text":"and we had worked with these very small,"},{"time":315948,"text":"breadbox-sized satellites in school,"},{"time":318042,"text":"but as we began to better\nunderstand the laws of physics,"},{"time":320593,"text":"we found that the quality of pictures"},{"time":322715,"text":"those satellites could take was very limited,"},{"time":325799,"text":"because the laws of physics dictate"},{"time":327503,"text":"that the best picture you\ncan take through a telescope"},{"time":330609,"text":"is a function of the diameter of that telescope,"},{"time":332848,"text":"and these satellites had a very small,"},{"time":334510,"text":"very constrained volume."},{"time":336216,"text":"And we found that the best picture we would"},{"time":338011,"text":"have been able to get looked something like this."},{"time":340496,"text":"Although this was the low-cost option,"},{"time":342741,"text":"quite frankly it was just too blurry"},{"time":344414,"text":"to see the things that make\nsatellite imagery valuable."},{"time":347983,"text":"So about three or four weeks later,"},{"time":350129,"text":"we met a group of engineers randomly"},{"time":352946,"text":"who had worked on the first"},{"time":354587,"text":"private imaging satellite ever developed,"},{"time":357028,"text":"and they told us that back in the 1970s,"},{"time":359146,"text":"the U.S. government had found a powerful"},{"time":361328,"text":"optimal tradeoff --"},{"time":362971,"text":"that in taking pictures at right\nabout one meter resolution,"},{"time":366059,"text":"being able to see objects one meter in size,"},{"time":368943,"text":"they had found that they could not\njust get very high-quality images,"},{"time":371634,"text":"but get a lot of them at an affordable price."},{"time":374527,"text":"From our own computer simulations,"},{"time":376503,"text":"we quickly found that one meter really was"},{"time":378508,"text":"the minimum viable product"},{"time":380272,"text":"to be able to see the drivers of our global economy,"},{"time":383351,"text":"for the first time, being able to count"},{"time":384912,"text":"the ships and cars and shipping\ncontainers and trucks"},{"time":387633,"text":"that move around our world on a daily basis,"},{"time":390457,"text":"while conveniently still not\nbeing able to see individuals."},{"time":394261,"text":"We had found our compromise."},{"time":395882,"text":"We would have to build something larger"},{"time":397486,"text":"than the original breadbox,"},{"time":399049,"text":"now more like a mini-fridge,"},{"time":400700,"text":"but we still wouldn't have to build a pickup truck."},{"time":403461,"text":"So now we had our constraint."},{"time":406085,"text":"The laws of physics dictated"},{"time":407842,"text":"the absolute minimum-sized\ntelescope that we could build."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411166,"text":"What came next was making the rest of the satellite"},{"time":414220,"text":"as small and as simple as possible,"},{"time":415961,"text":"basically a flying telescope with four walls"},{"time":418613,"text":"and a set of electronics smaller than a phone book"},{"time":421554,"text":"that used less power than a 100 watt lightbulb."},{"time":424992,"text":"The big challenge became actually taking"},{"time":426892,"text":"the pictures through that telescope."},{"time":429090,"text":"Traditional imaging satellites use a line scanner,"},{"time":432134,"text":"similar to a Xerox machine,"},{"time":433895,"text":"and as they traverse the Earth, they take pictures,"},{"time":436295,"text":"scanning row by row by row"},{"time":438491,"text":"to build the complete image."},{"time":440166,"text":"Now people use these because they get a lot of light,"},{"time":443170,"text":"which means less of the noise you see"},{"time":445016,"text":"in a low-cost cell phone image."},{"time":447752,"text":"The problem with them is they require"},{"time":450113,"text":"very sophisticated pointing."},{"time":452353,"text":"You have to stay focused on a 50-centimeter target"},{"time":454899,"text":"from over 600 miles away"},{"time":456651,"text":"while moving at more than\nseven kilometers a second,"},{"time":458883,"text":"which requires an awesome degree of complexity."},{"time":461632,"text":"So instead, we turned to a new\ngeneration of video sensors,"},{"time":465069,"text":"originally created for use in night vision goggles."},{"time":468160,"text":"Instead of taking a single, high quality image,"},{"time":471059,"text":"we could take a videostream"},{"time":472446,"text":"of individually noisier frames,"},{"time":475369,"text":"but then we could recombine"},{"time":477113,"text":"all of those frames together"},{"time":478579,"text":"into very high-quality images"},{"time":480575,"text":"using sophisticated pixel processing techniques"},{"time":483168,"text":"here on the ground,"},{"time":484689,"text":"at a cost of one one hundredth a traditional system."},{"time":487826,"text":"And we applied this technique"},{"time":488979,"text":"to many of the other systems on the satellite as well,"},{"time":491953,"text":"and day by day, our design evolved"},{"time":494793,"text":"from CAD to prototypes"},{"time":498282,"text":"to production units."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501170,"text":"A few short weeks ago,"},{"time":502827,"text":"we packed up SkySat 1,"},{"time":504678,"text":"put our signatures on it,"},{"time":506451,"text":"and waved goodbye for the last time on Earth."},{"time":508674,"text":"Today, it's sitting in its final launch configuration"},{"time":512155,"text":"ready to blast off in a few short weeks."},{"time":515216,"text":"And soon, we'll turn our attention to launching"},{"time":517558,"text":"a constellation of 24 or more of these satellites"},{"time":520589,"text":"and beginning to build the scalable analytics"},{"time":523139,"text":"that will allow us to unearth the insights"},{"time":525478,"text":"in the petabytes of data we will collect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528667,"text":"So why do all of this? Why build these satellites?"},{"time":532640,"text":"Well, it turns out imaging satellites"},{"time":535251,"text":"have a unique ability to provide global transparency,"},{"time":538961,"text":"and providing that transparency on a timely basis"},{"time":541587,"text":"is simply an idea whose time has come."},{"time":544998,"text":"We see ourselves as pioneers of a new frontier,"},{"time":548521,"text":"and beyond economic data,"},{"time":550285,"text":"unlocking the human story, moment by moment."},{"time":553886,"text":"For a data scientist"},{"time":555449,"text":"that just happened to go to space camp as a kid,"},{"time":558199,"text":"it just doesn't get much better than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560914,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563129,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}